VL  - 16
IS  - 2
SP  - 257
EP  - 274
PY  - 1981
DA  - 1981/06/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(81)90112-3
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407681901123
AB  - This paper is concerned with parameter identification and estimation in linear structural equation models. We consider a special class of models which arises naturally when we disaggregate economic relations. We show that substantial gains in identification and estimation efficiency for ‘macro’ economic parameters can arise from disaggregation and analysis of the resulting ‘micro’ model.
